---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Partnerships, CPD Alignment & Academic Review"
  description="Academia Europa welcomes collaboration with CPD/CE bodies, universities, and professional institutions."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Partnerships & Accreditation"
    title="Partnerships, CPD Alignment, and Academic Review."
    lede="Academia Europa is committed to building professional education that can be reviewed, documented, and aligned with relevant CPD/CE expectations where applicable."
  />

  <Section eyebrow="Academic Documentation">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>Each programme carries learning objectives, module outlines, faculty profiles, references, and versioning suitable for academic and professional review.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="CPD/CE Alignment" tone="ivory">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>Selected programmes may be submitted for CPD/CE recognition by relevant professional bodies, including review pathways familiar to CPD/CE organisations in Europe and internationally.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Institutional Collaboration">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>Academia Europa welcomes dialogue with universities, professional associations, specialist colleges, CPD/CE bodies, and academic reviewers.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Ethical Claims" tone="ivory">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>We do not claim accreditation we do not hold. Where a programme is under review or in the application process, we say so explicitly.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Institutional Profile">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>An institutional profile is available upon request for academic, partnership, or CPD/CE review.</p>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Our Institutional Office</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>
